JOHANNESBURG - Zimbabwean President Emmerson Mnangagwa has discussed regional and development issues with President Jacob Zuma. This was Mnangagwa's first state visit, since taking office in November. READ: Mnangagwa calls for unity as new Zimbabwe cabinet sworn in The two leaders also spoke about strengthening bilateral ties. Zimbabwe is one of South Africa’s top five trade partners on the continent. During his visit, Mnangagwa also addressed a high profile business conference. eNCA